Import pyttsx3 library
import pyttsx3
from pyttsx3 import speak
Why: pyttsx3 is used for converting text into speech (offline TTS engine).
speak() is used to directly speak the given text.
Installation: pip install pyttsx3

Print welcome message to console
print("welcome to ROBO SPEAKER")
Displays a greeting on the terminal.

Speak welcome message
speak("welcome to ROBO SPEAKER please enter your input")\

Converts the welcome text into speech.
Start an infinite loop
while True:
Continuously asks the user for input until they choose to exit.

Take input from the user
x = input("enter your word which has to be spoken('for exiting the program type exit'): ")
Reads text input from the user.
Check if the user wants to exit
if(x.lower() == "exit"):
Converts input to lowercase to handle case-insensitive exit.\

Exit sequence
print("exiting the program")
print("goodbye")